modules.description: Handles parsing and serialization of HTTP cookie date-time strings according to RFC 6265. Works with `Ptime.date` and `Ptime.time` tuples to represent moments in time. Use this module to convert between string representations and structured date-time values when setting or reading cookie expiration times.

This module processes HTTP cookies by parsing, constructing, and serializing `Set-Cookie` and `Cookie` headers, managing attributes like expiration, domain, path, secure, and same-site flags. It converts between raw header strings and structured cookie values, supporting client-side state management in HTTP clients and servers. A child module handles cookie date-time parsing and serialization using `Ptime.date` and `Ptime.time`, enabling precise manipulation of expiration times. For example, you can parse a `Set-Cookie` header into a typed value, modify its attributes, and serialize it back into a header for transmission.
